      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-coverage",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model adequately identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB use",
      "description": "The validated CFD model, employing SST k-omega turbulence closure and a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model, is credible for identifying the worst-case operating condition (maximum relative hemolysis index) across the five specified flow-rate and rotational-speed combinations representative of clinical CPB use. The claim scope is limited to comparative ranking of operating conditions; absolute NIH prediction accuracy is a secondary consideration. Acceptance is conditioned on RH < 1 relative to the predicate device at the identified worst-case point.",
      "scope": "Comparative hemolysis ranking across 5 operating points; Class II CPB device; MRL 2",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating that worst-case hemolysis conditions are identified and bounded relative to a predicate device"
