      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, blood analog properties) match CFD boundary conditions within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments conducted using porcine blood at 37°C with hematocrit 35±2%. Flow rates and rotational speeds match CFD boundary conditions within 3.1% maximum deviation. Temperature and fluid property correspondence documented in test protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted NIH within ±20% of experimental measurements at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean absolute error between CFD-predicted and experimentally measured NIH is 8.3% across 5 operating points. Maximum deviation is 14.7% at the 4 L/min, 2500 RPM condition. All predictions within the ±20% acceptance band. Worst-case operating condition ranking is consistent between CFD and experiment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
