      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, RH index) are directly relevant to the COU decision criterion and are measurable in both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and derived relative hemolysis index (RH). Both quantities are directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1) and are experimentally measurable via photometric plasma-free hemoglobin assay. The QoIs are standard in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device evaluation."
    },
